abstract: >-
  Reference implementation and research artifacts for machine-checkable AGI
  governance compliance: a LegalRuleML-compatible norm encoding
  (agi_governance_legalruleml.xml), the agiev evidence vocabulary and
  evidence-bundle schemas, and a deterministic compliance engine (v1.3)
  evaluating eight norms across six principles via ten evidence-linked
  indicators. Engine v1.1 added a corrected evaluation precondition (mandatory
  null/absent-field checking before threshold evaluation; paper Section 8.3);
  v1.2 added type-and-range guards, per-norm fault isolation, and
  absent-confidence handling; v1.3 enforces lifecycle-stage scoping and
  provenance presence. The repository includes the blind conformance evaluation
  (three independently prompted LLMs, 120/120 verdict cells; paper Section 8.4)
  under conformance/, and the multi-coder real-evidence bridgeability study
  (three coders including two external ISO/IEC 42001 auditors; strict-pass
  unanimity, generous-pass Fleiss kappa 0.709; paper Section 8.5) under
  public_study/, comprising the labeling instruments of all three coders, the
  coder agreement matrix, reliability-analysis scripts, the reconciliation log,
  and the prospective auditor-validation study kit.
references:
